In the first phase, the vaccine will be given to healthcare workers, the second phase will be provided to social care workers, the third phase will be provided to people over 65, and the fourth phase will be provided to the public.
The vaccine usually needs to be stored at a temperature of two to three degrees Celsius.  This will not be challenging to maintain in rich countries, but in poor and developing countries where resources are scarce and power is insufficient, storing them can be a daunting task. Detectives will review footage capturing events of September 21 at around 10am outside the KRA offices. A spot check by the Nation found patients lying helpless in beds with relatives preferring to transfer them to private hospitals The talks aim to reach consensus before referendum signatures are handed to IEBC.